				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Carts that don't have mappers with mirroring control can be soldered in different ways to use different types of mirroring (it's also possible to override the mapper and permanently set the mirroring). So yes, mirroring is hardwired in the sense that the software can't change the mirroring type as it runs (unless a mapper allows this), but the person making the cart can, using a soldering iron.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

