				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Tokumaru is right that discrete boards will usually have solder pads to select horizontal or vertical mirroring, though boards manufactured by Nintendo use the opposite nomenclature compared to the emulation community. Bridge the H pads to select horizontal arrangement (same as vertical mirroring), or bridge the V pads to select vertical arrangement (same as horizontal mirroring).<br /><br />Say you were to put Lawn Mower (mapper 0, 16 KiB PRG, 8 KiB CHR, vertical mirroring) on an Ice Climber board (NROM-128, horizontal mirroring). You'd open it up and see a pair of pads bridged with solder, marked V. You'd desolder that pad and solder the H pad for horizontal arrangement.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

