						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">NinToad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Luckily I'm working with MMC3.</div><br />Nothing to worry about then. AFAIK, only a couple of obscure MMC3 boards have hardwired mirroring, the vast majority of them leave mirroring selection to the mapper, so you just have to be sure to use the correct register(s) to select the type of mirroring you need.</div><br /><br />You're probably thinking about TLSROM which uses the CHR A17 line to control CIRAM A10.  So while most MMC3 boards toggle between Horizontal and Vertical mirroring, TLSROM MMC3 boards can toggle between single screen A/B similar to AxROM.</div>

					
